                        <p>Resolva a seguinte questão: Seja <m>f(x)=2x^2-3x+1</m>, calcule <m>f\left(\dfrac{\sqrt2}{3}\right)</m>.</p>
                            <solution>
                                <p><m>f\left(\dfrac{\sqrt2}{3}\right)=2\left(\dfrac{\sqrt2}{3}\right)^2-3\cdot\left(\dfrac{\sqrt2}{3}\right)+1=\dfrac{4}{9}-\dfrac{9\sqrt2}{9}+\dfrac{9}{9}=\dfrac{13-9\sqrt2}{9}</m></p>
                            </solution>
                    </li>

                    <li>
                        <p>Investigue os valores numéricos da função <m>f(x)=3x^2-4x+1</m> e determine:</p>
                        <ol marker="a">
                            <li><m>f(h)</m></li>
                            <li><m>f(h+1)</m></li>
                        </ol>
                            <solution>
                                <ol marker="a">
                                    <li><p>f(h)</p>
                                        <p><m>f(h)=3(h)^2-4(h)+1</m></p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li><m>f(h+1)</m>
                                        <p><m>f(h+1)=3(h+1)^2-4(h+1)+1</m></p>
                                        <p><m>=3(h^2+2h+1)-4h-4+1</m></p>
                                        <p><m>=3h^2+6h+3-4h-4+1</m></p>
                                        <p><m>=3h^2+2h+4</m></p>
                                    </li> 
                                </ol>
                            </solution>
